'Calling a script with unnamed arguments is a simple method of passing values into a VBScript
'Those values can then be parsed up within the script by reading the properties
'To run the code, execute the following in the command prompt:
'C:\ENTD261>cscript.exe args.vbs Classes

strUniv = WScript.Arguments.Item(0)
strClass = WScript.Arguments.Item(1)
wscript.echo strUniv & " and " & strClass &"  count=  " & WScript.Arguments.Count
